Trichet Says ECB Didn’t Pressure Portuguese Banks, Officials

-- B y   A n a b e l a   R e i s
-- 
2011-04-08T13:48:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-08/trichet-says-ecb-didn-t-pressure-portuguese-banks-officials.html
European Central Bank President
 Jean-Claude Trichet  said the ECB didn’t pressure Portuguese
officials or banks over a potential aid package for the nation.  “We didn’t force the banks to do anything,” Trichet told a
press conference today in Godollo,  Hungary . “We didn’t force
the government, the authorities or the various political
sensitivities in  Portugal  to do anything.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anabela Reis in Budapest at  areis1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jones Hayden at   jhayden1@bloomberg.net  